    Arsenophonus\n              -like organisms, as well as other members of the\n              Enterobacteriales\n              and a widespread association of\n              Bartonella\n              bacteria from bat flies of all five genera. Using the well-described host specificity of these flies and data on community structure from selected bacterial taxa with either vertical or horizontal transmission, we show that host/vector specificity and transmission mode are important drivers of bacterial community structure.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Wilkinson, David A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Duron, Olivier", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cordonin, Colette", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gomard, Yann", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ramasindrazana, Beza", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mavingui, Patrick", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Goodman, Steven M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tortosa, Pablo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Goodrich-Blair, H.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/0ca4c4f4654b1a7e95315d299343e228", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/8971d6391ea91daa6dc5bace16e639f19a40552b629265ea610d13b74345bcb5", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/XCKCNR6D", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/XCKCNR6D", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/9c752b74f8ed42eb1aa9ac76767bf099!/b293251-295724", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/26f7ce5dd404e33c6570edd4ba250d20", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "c